paragraphs.text:
%spark_m3.pyspark
#import dgd libs
import pandas as pd
#pd.set_option('display.', -1)

from dgd_analytics.preprocessing import AutoPreprocessor
from dgd_analytics.dgd_utils import DGDUtils
from dgd_analytics.automl import AutoML

import inspect
from hyperopt import fmin, hp, tpe
from hyperopt import SparkTrials, STATUS_OK
from pyspark import StorageLevel  

from pyspark.ml.classification import RandomForestClassifier, LogisticRegression, GBTClassifier

from pyspark.sql.types import *
from hyperopt import tpe

from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

task = z.input("task")
project = z.input("project")
model = z.input("model_name")
model_id = z.input("modelId")
history_id = z.input("historyId")

train_table = z.input("train_table")
valid_table = z.input("valid_table")
test_table = z.input("test_table")

feature_columns = z.input("features_columns")
output_columns = z.input("output_columns")
label_column = z.input("label_column")

mode = z.input("mode")
configuration = z.input("configuration")
auto_tuning_type = z.input("auto_tuning_type")

#Feature engineering
type_numerical_imputer = z.input("type_numerical_imputer")
type_string_imputer = z.input("type_string_imputer")

type_data_scaler = z.input("type_data_scaler")
type_data_transformer = z.input("type_data_transformer")

string_feature_encoder = z.input("string_feature_encode")
string_transform_strategy = 'stringIndexer' if string_feature_encoder == 1 else 'oneHotEncoder'

polynomial_degree = z.input("polynomial_degree")
nonlinear_feature = z.input("nonlinear_feature")

model_based_method = z.input("model_based_method")

max_missing_ratio_allow = z.input("max_missing_ratio_allow")
max_missing_ratio_allow = None if max_missing_ratio_allow == '' else max_missing_ratio_allow

max_string_distinct_value_allow = z.input("max_string_distinct_value_allow")
max_string_distinct_value_allow = None if max_string_distinct_value_allow == '' else max_string_distinct_value_allow
max_string_distinct_value_allow = max_string_distinct_value_allow - 2

max_correlation_allow = z.input("max_correlation_allow")
max_correlation_allow = None if max_correlation_allow == '' else max_correlation_allow

min_variance_allow = z.input("min_variance_allow")

auto_select_features_model_based = True if model_based_method != '' else False

imputer_parram = z.input("imputer_parram")

if auto_tuning_type == 'hold_out': #z.get("auto_tunning_type") == 'hold_out':
    valid_df = None
    train_ratio = None
    k_folds = None
elif auto_tuning_type == 'random_split': #z.get("auto_tunning_type") == 'random_split':
    train_ratio = z.input("train_ratio")
    k_folds = None
    valid_df = None
elif auto_tuning_type == 'cross_validation': #z.get("auto_tunning_type") == 'cross_validation':
    k_folds = z.input("k_folds")
    valid_df = None
    train_ratio = None
    
#Metrics
metric = z.input("metric")

#hyperparameter optimization
checkpoint_steps = z.input("checkpoint_steps") if mode == 'auto' else 1.0
data_subsampling_ratio = z.input("data_subsampling_ratio")
data_subsampling_ratio = data_subsampling_ratio if data_subsampling_ratio != '' else 1.0

search_algorithm = tpe.suggest

import re
features = list(re.sub('[\s+]', '', feature_columns).split(','))

#Get dataframe
sqlContext.sql("""use default""")
train_df = sqlContext.sql(train_table)
valid_df = sqlContext.sql(valid_table) if valid_table != '' else None
test_df = sqlContext.sql(test_table)

# is_product_selection = 0.0
# if 'upgraded_product' in train_df.columns:
#     is_product_selection = 1.0


import json
search_space = json.loads(z.input("search_space"))
print(search_space)
for model_space in search_space:
    for params in model_space:
        if params == 'featureSubsetStrategy':
            continue
        model_space[params] = eval(model_space[params])
        
max_trials = int(z.input("max_trials")) if mode == "auto" else len(search_space)
        
from pyspark import StorageLevel  
#allow_persist = StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK if z.input("allow_persist") == 'true' else None

down_sampling_ratio = z.input("down_sampling_ratio")

paragraphs.title: AutoML
paragraphs.text:
%spark_m3.pyspark
'''
    Arugments:
        - input_cols (list of str): input columns (features)
        - label_col (str): target variable column
        - metric (str): a string denoting pyspark ml metric
        - base_estimator (pyspark.ml.Estimator): a baseline pyspark Estimator to be used if not want to use auto_select_model
        - verbose (boolean): whether to show progress

        - auto_select_features (boolean): whether to perform feature selection
        - feature_max_missing_ratio_allow (float): the maximum ratio of missing values count over column length for a column not to be filtered out
        
        - auto_select_model (boolean): whether to perform bayesian search to obtain the best model on validation set
        - max_trials (int): total number of trial times when searching for the best model
        - included_models (list of pyspark.ml.Estimator): list of Model type to be searched
        - checkpoint_steps (int): number of steps to checkpoint
        - search_algorithm (tpe.random.suggest / tpe.suggest): the technique to select model (random search / bayesian optimization)
        
        - auto_profiling (boolean): whether to summary some information about the dataset (missing values, ...)
'''

automl = AutoML(input_cols=features, 
                label_col=label_column, 
                metric=metric,
                model_type = 'binaryClassification',
                verbose=True,
                auto_select_features_statistic_based=True,
                auto_select_features_model_based=False,
                feature_max_missing_ratio_allow=max_missing_ratio_allow, 
                feature_max_distinct_values=max_string_distinct_value_allow,
                feature_max_correlation_allow=max_correlation_allow,
                auto_select_model=True, 
                max_trials=max_trials, 
                string_transform_strategy = string_transform_strategy,
                impute_strategy = 'constant',
                checkpoint_steps=checkpoint_steps, 
                search_algorithm=search_algorithm,
                auto_profiling=False,
                history_id=history_id)


automl.set_custom_search_space(search_space)

'''
    Perform end to end training: profiling -> preprocessing -> feature selection -> model selection -> training -> evaluation
    Arguments:
        - train_df (pyspark.sql.dataframe.DataFrame): the training dataframe
        - valid_df (pyspark.sql.dataframe.DataFrame): the validation dataframe (if validation_type=hold_out)
        - test_df (pyspark.sql.dataframe.DataFrame): the testing dataframe
        - train_ratio (float): is only used when validation_type=random_split, determining the ratio of train set when split train-valid
        - n_cross_val_folds (int): is only used when validation_type=cross_validation
        - data_subsampling_ratio (float): sub-sampling ratio for training set (performance gaining but sacrificing accuracy)
        - persist_option (StorageLevel.x ): if None: no persist, if of pyspark Storage level option, persist train, valid, test set using this option
'''

automl.fit(train_df=train_df, valid_df=valid_df, test_df=test_df, 
            validation_type=auto_tuning_type, train_ratio=train_ratio, n_cross_val_folds=k_folds, 
            data_subsampling_ratio=data_subsampling_ratio,
            down_sampling_ratio=down_sampling_ratio,
            persist_option = StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)

paragraphs.title: Model Prediction
paragraphs.text:
%spark_m3.pyspark
automl = AutoML(input_cols=features, 
                label_col=label_column, 
                metric=metric)
                
automl.load_model("/work_zone/upsell_core/data_all/vmlp/{}_{}".format(re.sub(r"\s+", '_', project), int(model_id)))

if auto_tuning_type == 'random_split' or auto_tuning_type == 'cross_validation':
    train, valid = DGDUtils().split_train_valid(train_df, 0.7, seed = 42)
elif auto_tuning_type == 'hold_out':
    valid = valid_df
    train = train_df
else:
    print(auto_tuning_type, "is not supported")
    
no_sample = test_df.count()
sampling_ratio = 5000000/no_sample if no_sample > 5000000 else 1.0

if isinstance(down_sampling_ratio, (int, float)):
    print('\nDownsampling train data with ratio: (class 0 : class 1 = {}:1)'.format(down_sampling_ratio))
    train, sampling_beta = DGDUtils().down_sampling(train, label_column, down_sampling_ratio)
    
train = train.repartition(1024)
valid = valid.repartition(1024)
test_df = test_df.repartition(1024)

train_pred = automl.transform(train.sample(sampling_ratio))
valid_pred = automl.transform(valid.sample(sampling_ratio))
test_pred = automl.transform(test_df.sample(sampling_ratio))

def delete_var(var):
    try:
        del var
    except NameError:
        print("NameError: ", var)
        pass

delete_var(task)
delete_var(project)
delete_var(model)
delete_var(model_id)
